{
  "bookId": "heshanggong-laozi",
  "num": 28,
  "title": "第二十八章（反朴）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "知其雄，守其雌，為天下谿。"
    },
    {
      "text": "為天下谿，常德不離，"
    },
    {
      "text": "復歸於嬰兒。"
    },
    {
      "text": "知其白守其黑，為天下式。"
    },
    {
      "text": "為天下式，常德不忒，"
    },
    {
      "text": "復歸於無極。"
    },
    {
      "text": "知其榮，守其辱，為天下谷。"
    },
    {
      "text": "為天下谷，常德乃足"
    },
    {
      "text": "復歸於樸。"
    },
    {
      "text": "樸散則為器，"
    },
    {
      "text": "聖人用之則為官長。"
    },
    {
      "text": "故大制不割。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "雄以喻尊，雌以喻卑。人雖自知其尊顯，當復守之以卑微，去雄之強梁，就雌之柔和，如是則天下歸之，如水流入深谿也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人能謙下如深谿，則德常在，不復離於己。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "當復歸志於嬰兒，惷然而無所知也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 12
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "白以喻昭昭，黑以喻默默。人雖自知昭昭，明白當復守之以默默，如闇昧無所見，如是則可為天下法式，則德常在。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人能為天下法式，則德常在於己，不復差忒。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "德不差忒，則常生久壽，歸身於無窮極也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "榮以喻尊貴，辱以喻污濁。人能知己之有榮貴，當復守之以污濁，如是則天下歸之，如水流入深谷也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "足，止也。人能為天下谷，則德乃常止於己。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 8,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "復當歸身於質樸，不復為文飾。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 9,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "器，用也。萬物之樸散則為器用也。若道散則為神明，流為日月，分為五行也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 10,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人升用則為百官之元長也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-12",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 11,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人用之則以大道制御天下，無所傷割，治身則以大道制御情欲，不害精神也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
